article.description: Moss scores 15, leads Buffalo over Eastern Michigan 78-63
article.headline: Moss scores 15, leads Buffalo over Eastern Michigan 78-63
article.linkText: Moss scores 15, leads Buffalo over Eastern Michigan 78-63
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- Justin Moss scored 15 points and grabbed nine boards, leading four in double figures as Buffalo beat Eastern Michigan 78-63 on Wednesday night. Buffalo (16-9, 7-6 Mid-American) snapped a three-game losing skid and is in fourth place, two games back of MAC East Division leaders Bowling Green and Kent State. Jarryn Skeete hit back-to-back 3-pointers to stretch Buffalo's lead to 55-39 and the Bulls led by double digits the rest of the way. Moss scored 13 points in the second half while Shannon Evans finished with 14 points and Will Regan 13. Karrington Ward had a double-double with 21 points and 11 rebounds, and had five blocks to lead Eastern Michigan (16-10, 5-8). Mike Talley scored 15 points and Tim Bond chipped in 12 for the Eagles, who were outrebounded by the Bulls 46-35.
